<div class=" highlight hl-ipython2"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">__future__</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">division</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">featureScaling</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">arr</span><span class="p">):</span>
    
    <span class="n">maxxy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">max</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">arr</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">minny</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">min</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">arr</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">maxxy</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">minny</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">raise</span> <span class="ne">ValueError</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;min aand max same&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">rescaled_arr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">minny</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">maxxy</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">minny</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">arr</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">rescaled_arr</span>

<span class="c1"># tests of your feature scaler--line below is input data</span>
<span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">115</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">140</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">175</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="k">print</span> <span class="n">featureScaling</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
